or give general guidance on where to learn the click

00:30:50.880 --> 00:30:54.479
on like drill down interface function?

00:30:54.479 --> 00:31:00.079
Yeah, the, so the, the maps, I'll start at the top.

00:31:00.079 --> 00:31:04.280
The maps are from, let me go back up here.

00:31:04.280 --> 00:31:07.079
These maps are using collapsible tree.

00:31:07.079 --> 00:31:09.479
It's like, that's the package name.

00:31:09.479 --> 00:31:11.880
So there's a, there's a shiny binding

00:31:11.880 --> 00:31:13.280
that gives you the input.

00:31:13.280 --> 00:31:15.079
So you can use that to generate a modal

00:31:15.079 --> 00:31:18.880
that has the, the information for the thing

00:31:18.880 --> 00:31:20.479
that was clicked on.

00:31:20.479 --> 00:31:22.880
So that's how to do it here.

00:31:22.880 --> 00:31:28.280
For bar graphs, these are all done with Plotly

00:31:28.280 --> 00:31:30.680
and there's similarly, there's a, there's a binding

00:31:30.680 --> 00:31:33.880
for shiny, there's a click binding that you can use

00:31:33.880 --> 00:31:37.280
to reference the, for example, the row number

00:31:37.280 --> 00:31:39.479
of the dataset that corresponds to the bar

00:31:39.479 --> 00:31:41.079
that was clicked on.

00:31:41.079 --> 00:31:42.680
So it's a little finicky to set up,

00:31:42.680 --> 00:31:44.280
but once you get it, it's pretty reliable.

00:31:44.280 --> 00:31:49.079
That's, that's how we do it.

