00:33:29.280 --> 00:33:30.880
The only thing that's in performance plans

00:33:30.880 --> 00:33:33.880
has to do with using the data,

00:33:33.880 --> 00:33:37.280
not about getting a specific score or anything like that.

00:33:37.280 --> 00:33:40.280
So yeah, by mapping it on the org chart,

00:33:40.280 --> 00:33:45.680
there is like, you can see who supervises what group,

00:33:45.680 --> 00:33:49.680
but virtually no one uses it for that purpose

00:33:49.680 --> 00:33:52.079
because the data wouldn't be useful then if we did that.

00:33:52.079 --> 00:33:54.280
Like as soon as you create a standard

00:33:54.280 --> 00:33:56.880
that's going to be mandated

00:33:56.880 --> 00:33:59.079
or you create a bar that has to be cleared,

00:33:59.079 --> 00:34:01.479
then people find ways to clear it,

00:34:01.479 --> 00:34:04.479
even if that may not be how they actually feel.

